HEADWORD: Nyula
<hw>Ny*u"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A species of ichneumon (<spn>Herpestes nyula</spn>). Its fur is
beautifully variegated by closely set zigzag markings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>


